            <p>
               <milestone n="1" unit="line"/> [...] has sent me a copy of the letter [...] has permitted to use up [the water ...] 
the sluice gates and let them be [...] and let them be opened [...]. <milestone n="7" rend="break" unit="line"/> Philippos to Dionysios, 
greetings. [...] and that of Damis was attached to [...] five. If he/they come(s) [...] 
<milestone n="11" rend="break" unit="line"/> Maimachos and his men [...] let him use up the water [...] let the gates be lifted up [...] 
also the sesame [land ...] <milestone n="15" unit="line"/> has not been finished [...] to pay and [...] the head of [...]dros.
 <note>Translation: B. Van Beek in P.Petr.Kleon, p. 93, © Peeters</note> 
            </p>
